definition.value: Any ring assembly that is a compound with a structure based on two oxazole rings connected by a single bond.
A carboxamide resulting from the formal condensation of a carboxylic acid with the amino group of an amino acid.
Compounds containing a biotin (5-[(3aS,4S,6aR)-2-oxohexahydro-1H-thieno[3,4-d]imidazol-4-yl]pentanoic acid) skeleton.
Compounds containing two phenyl groups connected by an ethyl linker.
Compounds containing a pyridine nucleus substituted with one or more bromine atoms.
A monobromopyridine in which the bromo substituent is located at position 3.
A compound which binds and activates the prostacyclin receptor IP1, but has only partial efficacy at the receptor relative to a full agonist.
Compounds containing an imidazole ring fused to a benzoquinone.
An  arylacetylene that is acetylene in which the hydrogens are replaced by phenyl groups.
An aromatic ketone containing a benzoin (2-hydroxy-1,2-diphenylethanone) skeleton.
A cyclic tripyrrole derivative that consists of three isoindole-type units, with the connecting carbon atoms replaced by nitrogen. The parent of the class of subphthalocyanines.
A cyclic pentapyrrole derivative that consists of five isoindole-type units, with the connecting carbon atoms replaced by nitrogen. The parent of the class of superphthalocyanines.
Compounds containing a pyridine skeleton substituted by two amino groups.
